snippet.title: Lesson 33 - Creating a Service Taxonomy
snippet.description: In this lesson Mark Richards describes the types of services that exist in a typical microservices ecosystem and how to create a service taxonomy using annotations that will help organize, govern, and categorize your microservices. Stay tuned for more lessons in Software Architecture at https://www.developertoarchitect.com/lessons/.
